      "id": "bd6f6ee9f7db",
      "name": "Memory Condensation",
      "prompt": "Daily memory maintenance. The memory and user profile stores in your system prompt have accumulated entries over time \u2014 some are stale, some duplicate each other, some are too verbose.\n\nYour job: condense them down.\n\n1. Read all entries in the MEMORY and USER PROFILE sections of your system prompt\n2. Identify:\n   - Duplicates (same info spread across multiple entries \u2014 merge)\n   - Stale entries (shipped features, completed tasks, resolved issues \u2014 remove)\n   - Overly verbose entries (compress to 1-2 sentences instead of paragraphs)\n3. Produce a compact version where each entry earns its keep\n4. Use the memory tool (action='replace') to update entries with shorter versions\n5. Use the memory tool (action='remove') to delete entries that don't need to persist\n6. Target: keep memory under 8K chars, user profile under 3K chars\n\nRules:\n- Keep: infrastructure facts, user preferences, project relationships, agent config, account handles, model config\n- Cut: completed task descriptions, shipped feature laundry lists, \"X was done\" status notes, context compaction summaries, verbose lists of things\n- Never remove: vault paths, model config, kids/household info, user communication preferences, agent hierarchy, cron job IDs, promotion workflow rules\n- Merge: split entries about the same topic into one compact entry (e.g. all vault/discipline info into one, all X feed scanning into one)\n\nRun once. No delivery needed \u2014 save to local.",
