      "prompt": "Nightly vault summary. Write a structured daily note to ~/Documents/ObsidianVault/Daily/{today's date}.md.\n\n1. Read session exports from today in 0-Inbox/hermes-sessions/ \u2014 scan the first 40 lines of each to get the day's work.\n\n2. Check which projects were active (1-Projects/), what changed.\n\n3. Check 0-Inbox/ for any unprocessed items that should be called out.\n\n4. Write a Daily/{date}.md note with:\n\n```\n# {date}\n\n## Work completed\n- bullet list of what was built, shipped, tested\n\n## Projects touched\n- [[links to project notes]]\n\n## Open threads\n- anything left mid-flight\n\n## Decisions\n- notable decisions made today\n\n## Next\n- what's on the plate for tomorrow\n```\n\n5. Save the file. Deliver:local (no Telegram noise \u2014 Seth sees it in the Morning Brief).\n\nKeep it factual and compact. If no sessions ran today (weekend/silent day), write a minimal note and deliver [SILENT].",
